<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chap_coordinate_vectors_vector_spaces">
  <title>Coordinate Vectors and Coordinate Transformations</title>
  <introduction>
    <objectives>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            How do we find the coordinate vector of a vector <m>\vx</m> with respect to a basis <m>\CB = \{\vv_1, \vv_2, \ldots, \vv_n\}</m>?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How can we visualize coordinate systems?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How do we identify a vector space of dimension <m>n</m> with <m>\R^n</m>?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What properties does the coordinate transformation <m>\vx \mapsto [\vx]_{\CB}</m> have?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How are the coordinates of a vector with respect to a basis related to its coordinates with respect to the standard basis?
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </objectives>
  </introduction>
